      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(codex): keep mirrored history continuity for large context windows",
        "body": "Fixes #84084\n\n## What Problem This Solves\n\nFixes an issue where users resuming Codex legacy mirrored-history sessions with larger context windows could lose older mirrored continuity when the fallback regressed to the conservative rendered-context budget.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nThis adds regression coverage for both legacy mirrored-history fallback shapes: fresh Codex thread start without a native binding, and resume from a stale native binding. The tests assert that a runtime `contextTokenBudget` large enough to exceed the default 24k rendered-context cap preserves older budget-sensitive anchors while still excluding history already owned by the native Codex thread.\n\n## User Impact\n\nUsers with high-window Codex sessions get CI protection against regressions that would silently shrink mirrored-history continuity back to small-window behavior.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- `git diff --check`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.extension-codex.config.ts extensions/codex/src/app-server/run-attempt.test.ts -t \"runtime context budget\" --reporter=verbose`\n\nLocal limitation: `node scripts/run-tsgo.mjs -p test/tsconfig/tsconfig.extensions.test.json --incremental --tsBuildInfoFile .artifacts/tsgo-cache/extensions-test.tsbuildinfo` was attempted but did not complete within a 300s local timeout.",
